.TH "usb_initialize_gadget" 9 "usb_initialize_gadget" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_initialize_gadget \- initialize a gadget and its embedded struct device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" usb_initialize_gadget
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "struct usb_gadget *gadget "  ","
.BI "void (*release)(struct device *dev) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
the parent device to this udc. Usually the controller driver's
device.
.IP "gadget" 12
the gadget to be initialized.
.IP "release" 12
a gadget release function.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns zero on success, negative errno otherwise.
Calls the gadget release function in the latter case.
